1
00:00:00,417 --> 00:00:02,210
This is our land.

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:10,135
In the heart of Oregon, where the Desert meets the river, and time whispers stories of connections that have been here long before us.

3
00:00:10,593 --> 00:00:17,600
For generations, we have called this land home, understanding 
the intricate dance between life and the elements.

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:24,482
Water, the lifeblood of this land, flows from the mountains,
carving its path through the arid landscape.

5
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:32,115
Our rivers are a source of sustenance and a sacred entity, 
nourishing both the land and its people.

6
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:35,827
Water is not just a resource; it is a life source.

7
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,621
This land holds a wealth of knowledge.

8
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:44,961
The people learned to read its rhythms, using their knowledge and generational experience to adapt to climate change.

9
00:00:45,462 --> 00:00:52,844
They found ways to cultivate life, to coax sustenance from the earth,
respecting its limits and honoring its gifts.

10
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:59,851
Animals, our relatives, are interwoven into this tapestry of life.

11
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:05,273
They share the same water, the same earth, the same sky as we do.

12
00:01:05,523 --> 00:01:14,407
We understand the interconnectedness of all living things, recognizing that our survival is tied to the well-being of the entire ecosystem.

13
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:20,830
This is a story of respect, of understanding,
and a deep connection to the land.

14
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:30,757
A story that continues to unfold as our climate changes, carried on by the generations of all of us that inhabit this beautiful place we call home.
